#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/area/introduction.rst:7
msgid ""
"The *Area* lamp simulates light originating from a surface (or surface-"
"like) emitter. For example, a TV screen, your supermarket's neon lamps, a"
" window, or a cloudy sky are just a few types of area lamp. The area lamp"
" produces shadows with soft borders by sampling a lamp along a grid the "
"size of which is defined by the user. This is in direct contrast to "
"point-like artificial lights which produce sharp borders."
msgstr ""

